The paper focuses on analyzing and improving deep saliency models for visual attention prediction, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the representations learned by individual neurons, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses deep learning techniques to train and fine-tune the models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the differences between human and data-driven saliency models, which is related to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
